[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering testing setup**\n\nI'm thinking about the instruction to create a setup that goes beyond the typical test framework to really achieve meaningful coverage. It seems that setting up a local server and WebClient can help reach a baseline. I'll be careful to avoid adding any optional dependencies unless absolutely necessary, since the existing tests already accomplished the goal. It's essential to keep things simple and focused on what’s required for effective testing!\n\n**Evaluating OAuth2 dependencies**\n\nI’m thinking about the risks related to using \"OAuth2WebClient\" paths. It requires an optional dependency, io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2:5.0.1, but my baseline coverage doesn’t need it. However, I wonder if this might be contradictory. If the agent opts for OAuth2, it could make sense to proactively add that optional dependency to ensure full coverage. It feels crucial to keep it deterministic while also being mindful of potential needs!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_073553be9c842f8a016a3f097be81081949431dc0a7494ca91\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqPwmLPL-KXj9MwhZtDK6DNpfvhn6lHWcc1nQGMEu18TOeenfiW56wUkkJ4Qi6mgR5b71ywOXG9E86oLtTBV8DRkaBcLV-KAn7tN3zQQo6WaI1BinFD_ZBZ07etjML0x44qB8LTOLR4J5zzWbbZHfm4aNUsaSg7FvH7D898U0WEpn0HinZHg3Eri9H-DL7Q6M00Rklz5jYxt6cDl-tfpLdaoihhuZHZFKDjmTNK0sKik5u13HV6G4ZBwmWIkY5HVt_MiOZxcqI06l6lquxQXmv-ZfNqBFmbAwLM259Dv6JywPdUXxW1Sbhe-jCiwpVcqDoQ5ykpaPmjsmrkhjRWRhJKX7aIIpDUvIoEP5NIWn2NM3tmNCOjY8LQLFlDhmxFz8WE58JJSOeUTJSjmw0aKPzwhlJvA7pAGJSIgSIcg2yYaD-z5kNLouCqrCWdJ58Dkj4KIJi2d-2kJL3Y8zRDcJgrS43pKxjGF2em4GtMDxORv2Mh-A_N4PiDKLykzgHis28B9sr_jedXyHS_-PmOGXq7HmXyATnunCjYnAjBp502X8Wvt4aTh7MFaDlhECnLJ9DaXTExnc7J9HKff8tlniE3A8LzrUEizWMIpqCVlAgbxb_kApPWZ7pzrP0A889fBnIx-symKrX2h-riyJIJ1EZkaoBS2VFnsqAYNKLkmcLxRkke3IwbOnvDvaVu4KB4frQAp57DPpW0Ejfql5QUteiPVRAJuFbgfpBbmTbufNN13HY49e_xoSw38R8qhlm0GV