 required for effective testing!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating OAuth2 dependencies**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the risks related to using \\\"OAuth2WebClient\\\" paths. It requires an optional dependency, io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2:5.0.1, but my baseline coverage doesn’t need it. However, I wonder if this might be contradictory. If the agent opts for OAuth2, it could make sense to proactively add that optional dependency to ensure full coverage. It feels crucial to keep it deterministic while also being mindful of potential needs!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1 resolves Vert.x Core with Netty 4.2.2.Final; on JDK 25 native runs Netty needs explicit Unsafe/reflection system properties before reliable coverage is reachable.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"For JDK 25 native-image runs, configure the generated test project/nativeTest run to pass -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true before Vert.x/Netty initializes. Use a local 127.0.0.1 Vert.x HttpServer for WebClient coverage; no external service or Docker image is needed.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"OAuth2WebClient is part of the artifact but depends on optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2; baseline meaningful WebClient coverage does not require it, but tests that specifically exercise OAuth2 APIs would need that extra dependency.\",\n    \"The system-property need is tied to Java 25/Netty 4.2.x native runs; local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_073553be9c842f8a016a3f098b24c48194ae8b11748927d6b8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 924, "output": 1289, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 27301, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782516090873, "responseId": "resp_073553be9c842f8a016a3f097b4eb88194b9b3f0a0de441342"}, "toolResults": []}
